http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/NSUI-members-protest-in-front-of-ABVP-office/article14012101.ece

Following the suicide of Rohit Vemula, a Dalit research student in Hyderabad, members of the National Students Union of India (NSUI) staged a protest against Akhila Bharatiya Vidyarthi Parishad (ABVP) in front of its office today. A few protesters even pelted stones on the building and allegedly assaulted the ABVP State secretary.The incident happened at around 11 a.m. when 30-40 students belonging to NSUI came to the ABVP office on Seshadripuram main road and raised slogans. Basavesh Khore, ABVP State secretary, came down from the office and asked the protesters to leave the place.An alert was made to the jurisdictional police station and the police rushed to the spot and asked the NSUI and ABVP leaders to come to the police station. While some of them went to the police station, a few NSUI members who stayed back assaulted Basavesh and also pelted stones at the building. The window panes were shattered. Additional police force rushed to the spot and took some of the protesters into custody.Balaji, national coordinator for social media of ABVP, said, “The members at our office told them not to protest in front of the building. However, they assaulted the State secretary. ”Sandeep Patil, DCP (Central), said, “The NSUI members had gathered in front of the ABVP office to protest. One of them pelted stones on the ABVP office, breaking the window. We have arrested five members in this connection and have booked them under charges of criminal trespassing.”Meanwhile, another complaint was registered by ABVP member Prashanth where he had said that he was receiving threats from unknown callers for the past few days.